President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Makan Delrahim to the Department of Justice as Assistant Attorney General (Anti-Trust Division). Delrahim currently serves as Deputy Assistant and Deputy Counsel to the President. He has previous experience as a partner at a national law firm in Los Angeles, specializing in antitrust and intellectual property law. Delrahim has also served as Deputy Assistant Attorney General for the Antitrust Division at the Justice Department, as well as Commissioner on the U.S. Antitrust Modernization Commission. He holds a J.D. from George Washington University School of Law, an M.S. from Johns Hopkins University, and a B.S. from UCLA.